label("$2$", (0,2), E);
label("$-1$", (0,-1), E);
label("$-2$", (0,-2), E);
[/asy] The final Answer is 4
 ### Proof
 The period of the graph is $\frac{\pi}{2}.$  The period of $y = a \sin (bx + c)$ is $\frac{2 \pi}{b},$ so $b = \boxed{4}.$
